', 11, NULL, 'A compound sentence is made up of at least two independent clauses (and an independent clause refers to a clause that can stand alone as a complete sentence). These independent clauses are generally joined together using a joining word (such as and, or, but, so). Compound sentences appear everywhere, and they can be very useful while writing. (Hey, that last sentence was an example!)

This Compound Sentences pack is designed to enable students to create compound sentences by training students to select the appropriate joining word(s) to use in order to string together multiple independent clauses.

In this pack, which consists of seven activities, students will learn how to differentiate between joining words, gaining practice in determining the relationship between ideas and the construction of a compound sentence.

The seven activities altogether contain 55 items. The pack is expected to take roughly 90 minutes to complete. Of the seven activities, five are “starter” level, in which the specific joining word required will be provided. The remaining two are “intermediate” level, in which students will have to choose the required joining word among multiple options.
', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO unit_templates (id, name, unit_template_category_id, "time", grades, author_id, problem, summary, teacher_review, flag) VALUES (27, 'Appositives and Modifying Phrases | BETA', 5, 60, '---
