', 11, NULL, 'An appositive is a noun or noun phrase that is set beside another noun to describe it. While “appositives and modifying phrases” may sound complicated, we come across them everywhere -- and they certainly can make sentences sound far better.

This Appositives and Modifying Phrases pack is designed to introduce students to these grammatical concepts, preparing students to incorporate these concepts habitually into their writing.

In this pack, which consists of five activities, students will receive the opportunity to insert appositive and modifying phrases in different places within a sentence, in order to strengthen the sentence.

The five activities altogether contain 33 items. The pack is expected to take roughly 60 minutes to complete.', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO unit_templates (id, name, unit_template_category_id, "time", grades, author_id, problem, summary, teacher_review, flag) VALUES (25, 'Adverbs of Manner | BETA', 4, 50, '---
