', 11, NULL, 'Adverbs are words that modify adjectives, verbs, or other adverbs. They’re used all the time -- the car drove slowly, or the man laughed loudly, or the student practiced regularly.

This Adverbs of Manner pack is designed to enable students to use adverbs effectively in sentences by training students to combine sentences to include adverbs.

 In this pack, which consists of four activities, students will be motivated to think of how to use adverbs and combine short, choppy sentences in order to produce a stronger, better structured sentence.

The four activities altogether contain 28 items. The pack is expected to take roughly 50 minutes to complete. Of the four activities, three are “starter” level, in which the adverb required to join the sentence will be provided. The last activity is “intermediate” level, which will require students to transform an adjective into an adverb before joining the sentences.
', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO unit_templates (id, name, unit_template_category_id, "time", grades, author_id, problem, summary, teacher_review, flag) VALUES (8, 'Irregular Plural Nouns / Possessives', 4, 70, '---
- ''4''
- ''5''
