', 11, NULL, 'The Complex Sentences pack covers sixteen common subordinating conjunctions. Students will combing sentences using subordinating conjunctions to create grammatically strong complex sentences.

In starter activities, students are given the joining word to use as they combine the sentences. In intermediate activities, students are given multiple joining words and must choose the one that most accurately expresses the relationship between the two ideas.
', 'A complex sentence is made up of an independent clause (a clause that can stand alone as a complete sentence) and at least one dependent clause (a clause that can’t). Complex sentences can be created by using subordinating conjunctions such as although, since, and because, which we’ll refer to as joining words. With the usage of complex sentences, writing can improve dramatically.

This Complex Sentences pack is designed to guide students through the process of creating complex sentences by teaching students to select the appropriate joining word(s) to use in order to establish relationships and form meaningful connections between ideas.

In this pack, which consists of nine activities, students will learn how to differentiate between joining words, gaining practice in determining the relationship between ideas and the construction of a complex sentence. They’ll come to know better how to craft grammatically strong and well-structured sentences.

The nine activities altogether contain 63 items. The pack is expected to take roughly 70 minutes to complete. Of the nine activities, seven are “starter” level, in which the specific joining word required will be provided. The remaining two are “intermediate” level, in which students will have to choose the required joining word among multiple options.
', NULL);
INSERT INTO unit_templates (id, name, unit_template_category_id, "time", grades, author_id, problem, summary, teacher_review, flag) VALUES (2, 'Determiners', 4, 50, '---
